        Parameters:

        state - the state of the university
        location - the location of the university
        control - the type of school (e.g. private)
        numOfStuStart - the number of students starting range number
        numOfStuEnd - the number of students ending range number
        perFemStart - the percentage of students who are female starting range number
        perFemEnd - the percentage of students who are female ending range number
        satVerbalStart - the starting range for SAT verbal score
        satVerbalEnd - the ending range for SAT verbal score
        satMathStart - the starting range for SAT math score
        satMathEnd - the ending range for SAT math score
        priceStart - the starting range for price/expenses
        priceEnd - the ending range for price/expenses
        finAidStart - the starting range for financial aid percentage
        finAidEnd - the ending range for financial aid percentage
        numOfAppStart - the user gives
        perAdmitStart - the starting range for admitted students percentage
        perAdmitEnd - the ending range for admitted students percentage
        perEnrollStart - the starting range for enrolled students percentage
        perEnrollEnd - the ending range for enrolled students percentage
        academicScaleStart - the starting range for quality of academics
        academicScaleEnd - the ending range for quality of academics
        socialScaleStart - the starting range for quality of social
        socialScaleEnd - the ending range for quality of social scale
        lifeScaleStart - the starting range for quality of life scale
        lifeScaleEnd - the ending range for quality of life scale
        popMajor - an list of popular major or emphases at the university
